ch case studies, they detail innovation archetypes that effectively sidestep these pathologies and blend innovation with scaling. Readers will come away with conceptual models to drive progress in the social sector and tools for defining the future of their organizations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aNonprofit organizationsxManagement. 0aSocial entrepreneurshipzBangladeshvCase studies. 0aSocial entrepreneurshipzIndiavCase studies. 0aSocial entrepreneurship. 0aSocial responsibility of business. 4aimpact. 4ainnovation archetypes. 4ainnovation. 4apathologies. 4aproductive innovation. 4arelational problems. 4ascaling. 4astrategy. 4atechnical problems. 4auncertainty. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Nonprofit Organizations & Charities / General.2bisacsh1 aMair, Johanna, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311070369640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360099740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503600997423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503600997.jpg  a978-3-11-070369-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles